Source: ubuntu-rockchip-settings
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Maintainer: clsx524 <clsx524@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: ubuntu-rockchip-settings
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         u-boot-menu,
         cloud-init
Description: Ubuntu system settings for Rockchip devices
 Default system configuration for Ubuntu on Rockchip single-board computers.
 Includes cloud-init NoCloud pinning, u-boot-menu defaults and other settings.

Package: ubuntu-server-rockchip
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         ubuntu-rockchip-settings,
         ubuntu-server,
         cloud-init,
         openssh-server,
         udisks2,
         fwupd,
         modemmanager,
         network-manager
Description: Ubuntu Server for Rockchip devices
 Meta-package for Ubuntu Server on Rockchip single-board computers.
 Pulls cloud-init and other base server packages explicitly so apt-get
 autoremove does not strip them after the rockchip kernel is installed.

Package: linux-rockchip
Architecture: all
Description: Linux kernel meta-package for Rockchip devices
 Meta-package satisfying the linux-rockchip kernel flavour name.
 The actual kernel is installed separately via dpkg.

Package: ubuntu-desktop-rockchip
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         ubuntu-rockchip-settings,
         ubuntu-desktop,
         cloud-init,
         openssh-server,
         udisks2,
         fwupd,
         modemmanager,
         network-manager
Description: Ubuntu Desktop for Rockchip devices
 Meta-package for Ubuntu Desktop on Rockchip single-board computers.
 Pulls cloud-init and other base desktop packages explicitly so apt-get
 autoremove does not strip them after the rockchip kernel is installed.
